race.comment: The draw might send SIXTIES (2) forward this time though he looked brilliant winning from off speed fresh. Has big peaks and wins from the front and the back then, so he is versatile as well as talented and he might catch plenty of these out given how forward he was fresh. ROMANTIC ENCOUNTER (6) was never in the race behind him but he is far better suited now. Liked his run in the Stutt in the spring which was won on speed by WEST OF SWINDON (1) who then did too much in both the Guineas and the Carbine Club. If he can set a more even tempo he can give it a big shake. ASAKURA (9) next best as he chases a third straight win to kick off this campaign.
